e released is functioning well with all the customer platforms configurations accordingly to the requirements of the software.\r\n\r\nThough it’s a tough job to make, this could really determine whether your software application is applicable and can operate in different database, OS, browsers and even in mobile devices or networks. The right software configurations could also affect the resolution, internet speed etc. This non-functional testing is the way of preventing or even reducing failures of the software.\r\n\r\nTo know more about software compatibility testing, here are its types:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Browser compatibility testing</li>\r\n 	<li>Hardware</li>\r\n 	<li>Networks</li>\r\n 	<li>Mobile Devices</li>\r\n 	<li>Operating System</li>\r\n 	<li>Versions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Browser Compatibility Testing</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is usually done in a compatibility testing. A browser compatibility testing determine if the software application is compatible with the various kinds of browsers such as Firefox, Internet Explorer, Chrome etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Hardware</strong>\r\n\r\nThis compatibility testing checks the compatibility of the software among the hardware configurations.\r\n\r\n<strong>Network</strong>\r\n\r\nThe connectivity of our computers or mobile devices depends on the success in this kind of software compatibility. This one is focused on testing the application if it runs correctly on different networks whether using mobile data or a Wi-Fi.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Mobile Devices</strong><strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nOur mobile phones’ software must be checked if it is compatible with the various mobile platforms which include windows, android, iOS and a lot more.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Operating Systems</strong><strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nThis one focuses on testing if the application can run well with different operating systems like Windows, Linux, etc.<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nAll of this compatibility testing types is really necessary to achieve a good quality of your software/product. Therefore, every step beginning from the QA testing should be carefully and meticulously done to prevent damages or erroneous functions in software during the compatibility testing. Once all the testing is made, the customers will be the one to suffer the damage. Hence, compatibility testing process which is considered to be the last part of the testing, requires thorough review of a computer professional.','HOW ESSENTIAL IT IS TO HAVE A SOFTWARE COMPATIBILITY TESTING?','','publish','open','open','','essential-software-compatibility-testing','','','2017-11-08 12:56:36','2017-11-08 12:56:36','',0,'http://www.talcubator.com/?p=3125',0,'post','',0),(3126,4,'2017-11-08 12:56:21','2017-11-08 12:56:21','Compatibility is the ability of two things to work and connect without having any irregularity. That’s how computer system also functions. People from all over the world really make use of computers each and every minute of their lives. A world without computer would bring a huge chaos and every work will be paralyzed. Thus, the assurance that a computer is well-functioning can be made possible through a thorough software compatibility testing.\r\n\r\nSoftware testing and all other testing methodologies are essential and deliver the success in a computer system yet this one serves as the finishing touch on all the software testing procedures and is one of the most challenging among all the steps. Compatibility testing assures that the software released is functioning well with all the customer platforms configurations accordingly to the requirements of the software.\r\n\r\nThough it’s a tough job to make, this could really determine whether your software application is applicable and can operate in different database, OS, browsers and even in mobile devices or networks. The right software configurations could also affect the resolution, internet speed etc. This non-functional testing is the way of preventing or even